WEBVTT

00:00.266 --> 00:02.768
You're watching The Simpsons.

00:02.770 --> 00:05.771
You know your life sucks.
Just get drunk
like you always do.

00:05.773 --> 00:08.474
Catch all-new episodes Sundays
and check out
our other Fox programs--

00:08.476 --> 00:11.610
Brooklyn Nine-Nine,
Bob's Burgers <i>and</i> Family Guy.

00:11.612 --> 00:14.446
What is this,
and how can I make the rest
of my life about it?

00:14.448 --> 00:15.681
Only on Fox.

00:24.124 --> 00:25.290
D'oh!

00:25.292 --> 00:26.625
(tires screeching)

00:26.627 --> 00:28.293
(grunts)

00:28.295 --> 00:30.863
♪

00:40.473 --> 00:41.974
HOMER:
D'oh!

00:41.976 --> 00:44.043
♪

00:54.988 --> 00:58.657
♪ Tonight, tonight

00:58.659 --> 01:01.827
♪ I'll win at cards tonight

01:01.829 --> 01:04.163
♪ My flushes will be

01:04.165 --> 01:08.000
♪ Straight tonight

01:08.002 --> 01:12.004
♪ Lenny's gonna
dominate tonight ♪

01:12.006 --> 01:15.174
♪ Carl's gonna be
a little late tonight ♪

01:15.176 --> 01:17.843
♪ Tonight, tonight

01:17.845 --> 01:21.180
♪ I'll cheat them all tonight

01:21.182 --> 01:22.681
♪ When they're drunk

01:22.683 --> 01:27.853
♪ They don't play cards
quite right ♪

01:27.855 --> 01:29.188
♪ Tonight, tonight

01:29.190 --> 01:30.856
(bottle shatters)

01:30.858 --> 01:34.193
♪ I won't get
drunk tonight ♪

01:34.195 --> 01:37.529
♪ Without a beer,
my head will clear ♪

01:37.531 --> 01:41.033
♪ Tonight

01:41.035 --> 01:43.869
♪ It's fun to trick a rummy

01:43.871 --> 01:47.372
♪ To put liquor in his tummy

01:47.374 --> 01:50.375
♪ Your friendship's
a delight ♪

01:50.377 --> 01:53.712
♪ And you may
lose your sight ♪

01:53.714 --> 01:55.280
ALL:
♪ Tonight

01:55.882 --> 01:57.216
(burps)

01:57.218 --> 02:00.552
♪ Tonight, tonight

02:00.554 --> 02:03.388
♪ Band camp calls tonight

02:03.390 --> 02:06.725
♪ My demo goes online

02:06.727 --> 02:09.228
♪ Tonight

02:09.230 --> 02:11.296
♪

02:23.243 --> 02:25.410
♪ Tonight, tonight

02:25.412 --> 02:27.412
♪ My dreams come true tonight

02:27.414 --> 02:29.915
♪ Deposit's due tonight
♪ I'll take the
pot tonight ♪

02:29.917 --> 02:32.584
♪ I'll eat fondue tonight
♪ I'll spike your
brew tonight ♪

02:32.586 --> 02:34.486
ALL:
♪ Tonight!

02:37.257 --> 02:39.258
Moe, what the
hell is that?!

02:39.260 --> 02:41.927
Sorry. I missed
rehearsal.

02:41.929 --> 02:43.428
Damn it.

02:43.430 --> 02:45.330
Marge, I'm heading out!
Poker night!

02:46.766 --> 02:49.768
I don't want you losing
all our scrimpings!

02:49.770 --> 02:51.436
Don't worry, Marge.

02:51.438 --> 02:53.438
The real excitement for me
is staying within a budget.

02:53.440 --> 02:54.773
(snickers)

02:54.775 --> 02:57.109
This is just
a friendly game, right?

02:57.111 --> 02:59.611
Oh, super friendly.

02:59.613 --> 03:01.113
Suckers.

03:01.115 --> 03:02.614
Dad, Dad, Dad.

03:02.616 --> 03:05.450
I need two things: a
good-night hug and a favor.

03:05.452 --> 03:07.286
Mm.
To save time,

03:07.288 --> 03:08.787
I'll start
describing the favor.

03:08.789 --> 03:11.123
I've just been accepted
to the best band camp

03:11.125 --> 03:13.292
this side of
the Mississippi!

03:13.294 --> 03:14.793
Which side are we again?

03:14.795 --> 03:16.628
Doesn't matter!
It's a great camp.

03:16.630 --> 03:19.464
Notable graduates include
Pete Barbutti.

03:19.466 --> 03:20.632
Pete Barbutti?!

03:20.634 --> 03:22.634
Yes! Anyway, it's
a little pricey.

03:22.636 --> 03:24.469
So, if you win
big tonight,

03:24.471 --> 03:27.806
maybe you could help make
a little girl really happy.

03:27.808 --> 03:29.474
Don't worry, sweetie,
I'm gonna win.

03:29.476 --> 03:31.476
And you know why?

03:31.478 --> 03:35.147
I'm wearing my lucky T-shirt.

03:35.149 --> 03:37.149
(sighs)
It was such a shame

03:37.151 --> 03:39.885
he lost to
President Garfield.

03:41.321 --> 03:43.889
Oh, I'll fix this.

03:45.825 --> 03:46.992
There.

03:46.994 --> 03:48.393
(hums a tune)

03:49.329 --> 03:51.997
The maestro is here.

03:51.999 --> 03:53.832
(screams, crashes)

03:53.834 --> 03:55.167
Hey, who's the lady?

03:55.169 --> 03:56.501
What, are you kidding?

03:56.503 --> 03:58.670
This is Laney Fontaine,
Broadway legend.

03:58.672 --> 04:00.672
She starred
opposite Al Pacino

04:00.674 --> 04:02.674
in    <i>Does a Tiger</i>
<i>Wear A Necktie?</i>

04:02.676 --> 04:03.675
Ooh!

04:03.677 --> 04:05.010
Now I date Moe.

04:05.012 --> 04:07.012
He's got everything
I look for in a man:

04:07.014 --> 04:08.847
a current
liquor license.

04:08.849 --> 04:10.682
(chuckles)
Well, it and you

04:10.684 --> 04:13.919
are the two most precious
wrinkled yellow things I know.

04:14.687 --> 04:16.755
♪

04:22.362 --> 04:24.529
WOMAN (over headphones):
Three of a kind beats two pair.

04:24.531 --> 04:26.365
Straight beats three of a kind.

04:26.367 --> 04:28.033
Three beats two.

04:28.035 --> 04:29.368
Four beats three.

04:29.370 --> 04:30.602
(dog howling)

04:34.040 --> 04:36.208
HOMER:
Oh, my God.

04:36.210 --> 04:38.543
Full house.

04:38.545 --> 04:41.880
We're gonna win! That means
Lisa goes to band camp.

04:41.882 --> 04:44.216
As long as Homer
doesn't let them know

04:44.218 --> 04:45.717
how good his hand is.

04:45.719 --> 04:48.887
Then he'll blow the whole
damn thing to hell!

04:48.889 --> 04:50.555
That would
be terrible.

04:50.557 --> 04:53.392
Worst jammed-in
movie parody ever.

04:53.394 --> 04:55.961
Come on, Homer. Poker face.

04:57.897 --> 05:00.399
Aah! Stupid git!

05:00.401 --> 05:02.934
I raise, no calls,
pot goes to me.

05:02.936 --> 05:04.569
Hold on, Fat Folds Five.

05:04.571 --> 05:06.071
(stammers)

05:06.073 --> 05:08.974
I see your raise,
and I raise this.

05:09.909 --> 05:11.576
Is that real?

05:11.578 --> 05:13.245
Won it for cinematography.

05:13.247 --> 05:16.415
Invented a new kind of Steadicam
that's mounted on a dog.

05:16.417 --> 05:19.251
That's five grand to you.

05:19.253 --> 05:21.920
So, are you in, or are you...

05:21.922 --> 05:23.588
(groans)

05:23.590 --> 05:26.425
While I'm out, no one
look at my cards or my boobs.

05:26.427 --> 05:27.759
(groans)

05:27.761 --> 05:30.429
Aw. Don't she black out
like an angel?

05:30.431 --> 05:32.264
Queens beat jacks.

05:32.266 --> 05:33.765
No one heard
that. I'm in.

05:33.767 --> 05:36.168
(hums a tune)

05:40.773 --> 05:43.342
Okay, Homer.
Moment of truth.

05:46.279 --> 05:48.947
Oh, four of a kind!
Hey, honey, you won!

05:48.949 --> 05:49.948
Huh?

05:49.950 --> 05:51.450
I lost.

05:51.452 --> 05:53.785
I lost everything.

05:53.787 --> 05:55.787
We're gonna
celebrate, Moe.

05:55.789 --> 05:57.289
What's Springfield's
version of Sardi's?

05:57.291 --> 05:58.957
Uh, Hardee's.

05:58.959 --> 06:02.127
I know a nice booth under a
picture of a hamburger. Heh.

06:02.129 --> 06:05.130
Aw, come on, Homer.
I'll drive you home.

06:05.132 --> 06:06.631
(imitates engine revving)

06:06.633 --> 06:08.800
Hey, off we go!

06:08.802 --> 06:10.969
Vroom, vroom, vroom.

06:10.971 --> 06:12.304
(imitates engine chugging)

06:12.306 --> 06:13.972
(door closes)

06:13.974 --> 06:16.308
WOMAN: You've completed
Poker: A Beginner's Guide.

06:16.310 --> 06:19.311
Now go out there and win.

06:19.313 --> 06:21.380
I bid two bucks.

06:28.988 --> 06:31.656
♪

06:31.658 --> 06:33.225
(floor creaking softly)

06:38.331 --> 06:39.831
(belt cracks)
(gasps) What was that?

06:39.833 --> 06:43.502
Those aren't the tiptoes
of a successful gambler.

06:43.504 --> 06:45.337
How much did you lose?

06:45.339 --> 06:46.838
$5,000.

06:46.840 --> 06:48.173
(high-pitched chirping)

06:48.175 --> 06:49.674
Whoa, I never heard that noise.

06:49.676 --> 06:51.510
(sobbing)

06:51.512 --> 06:53.011
(Marge continues sobbing)

06:53.013 --> 06:54.346
I'm just sayin',
doesn't look like

06:54.348 --> 06:57.249
band camp is
in the cards.

06:58.684 --> 07:00.752
(playing jazz)

07:03.022 --> 07:05.090
Hey, this is
my thing now.

07:07.527 --> 07:09.027
So easy.

07:09.029 --> 07:10.529
Guys, I need help
with a plan.

07:10.531 --> 07:12.364
Hey, what about
a reverse mortgage?

07:12.366 --> 07:15.367
I saw a commercial for one where
an old lady gave a thumbs-up

07:15.369 --> 07:17.569
and it turned into money,
which filled up the screen.

07:17.571 --> 07:19.037
The entire screen?

07:19.039 --> 07:20.872
Swear to God.

07:20.874 --> 07:23.875
Hey, Homer, here's a thought:
invite Laney over for dinner.

07:23.877 --> 07:26.878
Show her your crummy home,
your unhappy kids.

07:26.880 --> 07:29.047
Anyone with a heart
would take pity.

07:29.049 --> 07:31.049
Finally, my sucky life pays off.

07:31.051 --> 07:32.884
Do you guys
think she'll buy it?

07:32.886 --> 07:35.554
Oh, yeah. Your whole house,
uh, it smells like a basement.

07:35.556 --> 07:37.389
I've always
hated your rugs.

07:37.391 --> 07:39.891
Yeah... Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Why you have to go there, man?

07:39.893 --> 07:41.393
He has such
beautiful floors.

07:41.395 --> 07:43.562
Why must he
hide them? Why?

07:43.564 --> 07:44.896
LANEY:
There I am,

07:44.898 --> 07:46.731
on the main stage at Caesar's,

07:46.733 --> 07:48.567
about to sing
"Do You Love Me,"

07:48.569 --> 07:51.236
when who do I see
sitting in the wings?

07:51.238 --> 07:53.071
Your boyfriend King Tut?

07:53.073 --> 07:54.906
No. Jack Jones.

07:54.908 --> 07:56.741
High on his success from
"Wives and Lovers"

07:56.743 --> 07:59.744
with eyes for yours truly.

07:59.746 --> 08:03.081
But you'd just accepted
a proposal from Mike Connors.

08:03.083 --> 08:04.749
Which I broke off.

08:04.751 --> 08:07.252
Let's just say
Mannix was the one man

08:07.254 --> 08:09.087
I had to nix.

08:09.089 --> 08:11.089
(laughs):
Oh!

08:11.091 --> 08:12.757
Oh, that's rich!

08:12.759 --> 08:13.758
Oh, my God.

08:13.760 --> 08:14.926
That's going in your book.

08:14.928 --> 08:16.795
Please tell me
you're writing a book.

08:16.797 --> 08:18.597
(choking)

08:18.599 --> 08:19.931
(grunts)
Sit down, boy.

08:19.933 --> 08:21.433
We're trying
to show this dame

08:21.435 --> 08:22.934
that we're deserving
of her pity.

08:22.936 --> 08:24.269
Where's that crutch I gave you?

08:24.271 --> 08:26.104
There's nothing wrong
with my leg.

08:26.106 --> 08:27.105
There will be.

08:27.107 --> 08:28.273
D'oh!

08:28.275 --> 08:30.675
Ow! Ow, my leg!

08:31.944 --> 08:35.280
(sobbing):
Oh! Oh, my leg.

08:35.282 --> 08:36.948
Oh!

08:36.950 --> 08:40.952
Who would take $5,000
from such a miserable creature?

08:40.954 --> 08:43.455
(sobbing)

08:43.457 --> 08:46.124
Laney, I know
it's your night off,

08:46.126 --> 08:48.460
but would you like to
sing a song for us?

08:48.462 --> 08:50.629
You don't have to ask me twice.

08:50.631 --> 08:54.366
♪ I'm just a
Broadway lady ♪

08:56.969 --> 09:00.539
♪ Dancing on my aching feet

09:03.142 --> 09:06.144
♪ Avoiding any foods
with wheat ♪

09:06.146 --> 09:10.315
♪ And no drinking pre-show

09:10.317 --> 09:11.983
It's okay if the
producer don't

09:11.985 --> 09:15.320
♪ Know.

09:15.322 --> 09:17.556
(playing jazz)

09:20.993 --> 09:24.329
Wow. You know your way
around a horn, kid.

09:24.331 --> 09:26.164
Oh, listen,
I don't want to gush,

09:26.166 --> 09:27.832
but I have all your albums.

09:27.834 --> 09:29.167
Laney Sings The Blues,

09:29.169 --> 09:30.669
Electric Laney Land,

09:30.671 --> 09:32.170
Laney Butchers The Beatles.

09:32.172 --> 09:33.838
Ooh, and my favorite,

09:33.840 --> 09:36.508
Rehab Yourself
A Merry Little Christmas.

09:36.510 --> 09:38.009
I'll tell you
what, Marge.

09:38.011 --> 09:40.845
I'll wipe the slate
clean on one condition.

09:40.847 --> 09:42.347
I want you to
give Lisa to me.

09:42.349 --> 09:43.848
(grumbles)

09:43.850 --> 09:45.750
Uh, for a month or so.

09:49.188 --> 09:50.689
I see.

09:50.691 --> 09:54.025
Get out. I never
want to see you again.

09:54.027 --> 09:55.193
Let me explain.

09:55.195 --> 09:57.529
Listen, lady,
you can't take a daughter

09:57.531 --> 09:59.698
from a mother
unless you're a bigger star

09:59.700 --> 10:01.032
and this is
a third-world country.

10:01.034 --> 10:02.867
Marge,

10:02.869 --> 10:06.204
I know this sounds nuts, but
I never had the joy you have.

10:06.206 --> 10:08.540
A child to hug me
at the end of the day

10:08.542 --> 10:11.209
or-or a chance
to pass along what I know.

10:11.211 --> 10:14.713
I'm going out on tour, and she's
got all the makings of a star:

10:14.715 --> 10:17.215
talent, smarts and
a star-shaped head.

10:17.217 --> 10:19.384
Perhaps you didn't hear me.

10:19.386 --> 10:21.386
Here's your coat.

10:21.388 --> 10:23.221
Mom, Mom.

10:23.223 --> 10:26.725
Mom, please. You were gonna let
me go to band camp for a month,

10:26.727 --> 10:29.728
where people break curfew
and exchange reeds.

10:29.730 --> 10:33.064
But this? This is the
opportunity to live my dream.

10:33.066 --> 10:36.067
Come on, how many chances
in life do you get for that?

10:36.069 --> 10:37.235
GRAMPA:
None!

10:37.237 --> 10:40.805
I've been here,
I've just been quiet.

10:41.907 --> 10:43.308
♪

10:47.913 --> 10:50.915
(sighs)
I guess I can't deny you this.

10:50.917 --> 10:52.250
All right.
(gasps)

10:52.252 --> 10:53.918
Oh, thanks, Mom!

10:53.920 --> 10:56.921
And, Mom, if you have any doubts
how a showbiz kid will turn out,

10:56.923 --> 10:58.423
just look at
all of them!

10:58.425 --> 10:59.991
(groans)

11:01.093 --> 11:02.761
(tires screech)

11:02.763 --> 11:04.763
Mom, I appreciate this
so much.

11:04.765 --> 11:07.265
You'll be the first person
I thank at the Tonys

11:07.267 --> 11:09.601
after the great Angela Lansbury.

11:09.603 --> 11:11.102
Bye.

11:11.104 --> 11:12.771
(smoke hisses)

11:12.773 --> 11:14.339
(tires screech)

11:17.443 --> 11:20.011
(tires screech)

11:22.114 --> 11:25.116
Good night, kid.

11:25.118 --> 11:27.118
Would you read to me
before I go to bed?

11:27.120 --> 11:29.120
Anne of Green Gables?

11:29.122 --> 11:31.122
I did the
audiobook on this.

11:31.124 --> 11:33.458
If chapter ten sounds
like it was Peter Falk,

11:33.460 --> 11:35.460
it's because it was.

11:35.462 --> 11:38.463
So I guess you don't want
to read it again.

11:38.465 --> 11:40.799
How 'bout I give you
some showbiz advice?

11:40.801 --> 11:43.468
Every piece of advice
someone gives you

11:43.470 --> 11:45.637
will turn out to be wrong.

11:45.639 --> 11:48.807
Particularly wrong are people
like me, who seem knowledgeable.

11:48.809 --> 11:50.875
Aw, she's already out.

11:51.811 --> 11:54.145
(phone rings)

11:54.147 --> 11:56.147
MOE: You watching Channel Six
right now?

11:56.149 --> 11:57.649
Hurry up! Hurry up! Aw!

11:57.651 --> 11:59.818
Nah, too late.
The cops cleaned it up.

11:59.820 --> 12:01.820
(piano playing)

12:01.822 --> 12:04.823
Chazz Busby.
My director.

12:04.825 --> 12:07.659
The man who's ruined more
productions than flu season.

12:07.661 --> 12:09.661
Laney! My star, my muse,

12:09.663 --> 12:11.830
my God, what have you
done to your face?

12:11.832 --> 12:13.164
(Laney and Chazz laugh)

12:13.166 --> 12:14.332
Who's the lampshade?

12:14.334 --> 12:16.000
This is Lisa Simpson,

12:16.002 --> 12:18.503
the sax prodigy who's gonna
blow life into my act.

12:18.505 --> 12:19.671
Show him, kid.

12:19.673 --> 12:21.206
(plays three notes)

12:21.208 --> 12:23.174
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa! I wanted an audition,

12:23.176 --> 12:25.009
not a recital.
You're in, kid.

12:25.011 --> 12:26.745
I made it in Hartford.

12:29.682 --> 12:31.015
MARGE:
Are you sure

12:31.017 --> 12:33.017
you set it up right?
Yes!

12:33.019 --> 12:35.353
Then why aren't
we Skyping?

12:35.355 --> 12:37.522
I don't know.
Maybe Lisa's drugged-out.

12:37.524 --> 12:39.858
My daughter is not drugged-out.

12:39.860 --> 12:42.527
Maybe she's just sleeping late
after partying at discotheques.

12:42.529 --> 12:45.196
How do you know about
all-night discotheques?

12:45.198 --> 12:47.699
We have Disco Stu
in this town, Mom.

12:47.701 --> 12:49.701
He's a resource.
Use him.

12:49.703 --> 12:51.703
(Skype ringtone plays)

12:51.705 --> 12:54.038
How are you,
sweetie?

12:54.040 --> 12:55.540
(gravelly):
I'm good, I'm good.

12:55.542 --> 12:57.041
What happened to your voice?

12:57.043 --> 12:58.209
I don't know.

12:58.211 --> 12:59.878
Late rehearsals,
cheap root beer.

12:59.880 --> 13:01.713
(coughing)

13:01.715 --> 13:05.383
(normal voice): But I'm great!
We're heading to New York!

13:05.385 --> 13:06.551
(blows)

13:06.553 --> 13:07.886
Who's watching you?

13:07.888 --> 13:09.220
Sonny and Stix.

13:09.222 --> 13:11.389
(playing mellow jazz)

13:11.391 --> 13:13.391
Do I hear syncopation?

13:13.393 --> 13:15.560
Lisa, Lisa, I was thinking
maybe you could

13:15.562 --> 13:17.562
come home a little early and...

13:17.564 --> 13:19.731
I'm sorry. I got to go.
Our take five is over,

13:19.733 --> 13:22.400
and jazz is all about
following the rules, you know.

13:22.402 --> 13:24.903
Come on, guys.
Don't I get a puff?

13:24.905 --> 13:25.637
(gasps)

13:27.573 --> 13:29.407
I  <i>really</i>have
the munchies.

13:29.409 --> 13:30.742
(crunching)

13:30.744 --> 13:32.076
Bye!

13:32.078 --> 13:33.745
We've got to
get her back.

13:33.747 --> 13:35.914
Pack your things. We're
heading for New York.

13:35.916 --> 13:38.149
We should get a place there.
We go so often.

13:43.756 --> 13:45.490
♪

13:51.764 --> 13:54.933
I can't believe
I'm gonna be performing here.

13:54.935 --> 13:57.001
(dramatic music playing)

14:02.775 --> 14:05.443
I already got <i>my</i> ticket!

14:05.445 --> 14:07.445
LISA (nervously):
Ah, so many seats.

14:07.447 --> 14:09.113
(car sputtering)
Damn it!

14:09.115 --> 14:11.115
Lousy electric car.

14:11.117 --> 14:13.618
Dad, just 'cause it got
hit by lightning that time

14:13.620 --> 14:15.119
doesn't make it
electric.

14:15.121 --> 14:17.689
Shut up, boy.

14:22.461 --> 14:24.128
How may I help thee,
friends?

14:24.130 --> 14:27.298
Our car... broketh down.

14:27.300 --> 14:29.634
(gasps) Springfield
Englisher accent?

14:29.636 --> 14:33.972
You must know my ultra-liberal
cousin Ned Flanders.

14:33.974 --> 14:36.474
Oh, he's brought such shame
to our family

14:36.476 --> 14:38.977
with his lip hair
and two marriages.

14:38.979 --> 14:42.547
And do you know
he's left-handed?

14:44.650 --> 14:46.551
(wheels creaking)

14:47.820 --> 14:50.822
Um, can I please
use the, uh,

14:50.824 --> 14:52.824
little bearded
boys' room?

14:52.826 --> 14:53.992
(horse neighs)

14:53.994 --> 14:56.227
♪

15:06.505 --> 15:07.839
(humming)

15:07.841 --> 15:09.674
How deep
did thou diggest?

15:09.676 --> 15:11.175
30 hands.

15:11.177 --> 15:14.012
With God's grace,
it will be enough.

15:14.014 --> 15:17.348
♪ Don't know why

15:17.350 --> 15:19.350
♪ There's no sun up

15:19.352 --> 15:20.685
♪ In the...

15:20.687 --> 15:23.354
♪ In the... in the...

15:23.356 --> 15:24.689
How about "in the sky"?!

15:24.691 --> 15:25.857
The sky!

15:25.859 --> 15:27.358
You ought to
know, sweetheart.

15:27.360 --> 15:29.527
You were there when
God created it.

15:29.529 --> 15:31.529
Eh, go shave a coconut.

15:31.531 --> 15:33.197
(gasping)

15:33.199 --> 15:35.867
I turned down <i>Transformers</i>
<i>on Broadway</i> for this?

15:35.869 --> 15:37.869
I was a Megatron-sized fool!

15:37.871 --> 15:40.872
Kristen Chenoweth was set
to play Sam Witwicky's mother.

15:40.874 --> 15:43.207
This is how mad I am!
Fade to black!

15:43.209 --> 15:44.876
You can't be serious!

15:44.878 --> 15:46.544
I said fade!

15:46.546 --> 15:49.213
Everyone, meet me back here
in however long it takes

15:49.215 --> 15:50.715
to wake up
from five Valium.

15:50.717 --> 15:51.883
On the dot!

15:51.885 --> 15:53.451
(horns honking)

15:55.888 --> 15:58.222
Hey, man, how'd
you get that seat?

15:58.224 --> 16:00.625
They thought
I was pregnant.

16:02.728 --> 16:04.629
(indistinct chatter)

16:08.233 --> 16:10.401
It's showtime, Laney.
Time to see if there's still

16:10.403 --> 16:14.472
a spark left in that smoldering
Duraflame log you call a career.

16:15.908 --> 16:17.241
Hey, Laney.

16:17.243 --> 16:18.910
Moe, I need you.

16:18.912 --> 16:21.913
To make me feel confident,
strong and beautiful.

16:21.915 --> 16:24.415
Boy, I'm not real good at
boosting self-esteem there.

16:24.417 --> 16:27.085
But, uh, if you make a
mistake, I can fire my gun.

16:27.087 --> 16:29.587
And that's what the critics
will be yappin' about tomorrow.

16:29.589 --> 16:30.655
(chuckles)

16:36.428 --> 16:38.096
That's not
encouragement!

16:38.098 --> 16:40.598
Those are
your lyrics!

16:40.600 --> 16:43.434
(applause, piano playing)
♪ I had a dream

16:43.436 --> 16:47.772
♪ A dream about you, baby

16:47.774 --> 16:51.776
♪ It's gonna come true, baby

16:51.778 --> 16:55.279
♪ They think
that we're through ♪

16:55.281 --> 16:59.350
♪ But, baby...

17:01.620 --> 17:04.288
♪ You'll be swell

17:04.290 --> 17:06.124
♪ You'll be great

17:06.126 --> 17:09.127
♪ Gonna have the whole world
on a... ♪

17:09.129 --> 17:11.462
♪ On a...

17:11.464 --> 17:12.797
Plate!

17:12.799 --> 17:14.298
(crowd cheering)

17:14.300 --> 17:15.967
Cheering for someone
getting a word right.

17:15.969 --> 17:17.502
That is a low bar.

17:17.504 --> 17:18.469
(panting)

17:18.471 --> 17:19.804
Four tickets, please.

17:19.806 --> 17:21.639
I'm sorry, ma'am.
The show is sold out

17:21.641 --> 17:23.307
for reasons
that elude me.

17:23.309 --> 17:24.809
My daughter's in there.

17:24.811 --> 17:26.477
Eh, we all got
our problems.

17:26.479 --> 17:28.980
I'm a ticket seller
for a dying art form.

17:28.982 --> 17:33.651
Hey, uh, you're a
union man, right?

17:33.653 --> 17:35.319
Brother?

17:35.321 --> 17:36.654
Why didn't you say so?

17:36.656 --> 17:38.656
I have no choice now
but to be corrupt.

17:38.658 --> 17:39.891
In you go.

17:41.326 --> 17:44.328
LANEY:
♪ Everything's gonna be

17:44.330 --> 17:46.664
♪ Bright lights and lollipops

17:46.666 --> 17:48.733
(playing jazz solo)

17:51.003 --> 17:54.005
(crowd cheering)

17:54.007 --> 17:56.007
Come on, let's
sneak her out.

17:56.009 --> 17:59.010
Under the guise of soliciting
for Broadway Cares.

17:59.012 --> 18:01.079
(coins jingling)

18:02.514 --> 18:03.848
Wait. Wait, Homer.

18:03.850 --> 18:05.183
Look at our little girl.

18:05.185 --> 18:06.684
She's got chops.

18:06.686 --> 18:08.853
Honest-to-goodness chops.

18:08.855 --> 18:11.689
Yeah. Letting our daughter
go on the road

18:11.691 --> 18:14.525
with an 80-year-old diva
and some sketchy jazz guys

18:14.527 --> 18:17.361
was the best decision
we ever made.

18:17.363 --> 18:21.199
♪ Everything's coming up roses

18:21.201 --> 18:25.536
♪ For me and for you!

18:25.538 --> 18:27.105
(crowd cheering)

18:28.040 --> 18:29.607
(whoops)

18:36.548 --> 18:38.382
Mom, that was the greatest
night of my life!

18:38.384 --> 18:39.550
MILHOUSE:
Hey!

18:39.552 --> 18:41.552
When does the
show start?

18:41.554 --> 18:43.888
It did, and it was wonderful.

18:43.890 --> 18:46.557
Eh, she's been bitten
by the showbiz bug.

18:46.559 --> 18:49.227
And when that happens,
only working with Bruce Willis

18:49.229 --> 18:50.461
can extinguish it.

18:52.397 --> 18:53.731
(giggles)

18:53.733 --> 18:56.234
(sighs) Okay. Just
finish out the tour.

18:56.236 --> 18:58.803
We'll see you
in Pittsfield.

19:03.742 --> 19:05.409
No way!

19:05.411 --> 19:07.578
Pittsfield ain't happening
for this little scene stealer.

19:07.580 --> 19:10.915
I love you, Lisa, but you got
a bigger ovation than me.

19:10.917 --> 19:13.417
So we can never share
the same stage again.

19:13.419 --> 19:15.586
What? How can you say that?

19:15.588 --> 19:17.588
Showbiz lesson
number seven:

19:17.590 --> 19:19.590
just when things
are going great,

19:19.592 --> 19:21.592
they pull the rug out
from under you.

19:21.594 --> 19:23.427
Bad news, Laney.
We're shutting down.

19:23.429 --> 19:26.097
Never cleared the rights to
"Everything's Coming Up Roses."

19:26.099 --> 19:27.265
See what I mean?

19:27.267 --> 19:29.100
Also, we're gonna need
that rug.

19:29.102 --> 19:31.936
(grunts)
(shouts)

19:31.938 --> 19:33.437
(sniffles)

19:33.439 --> 19:35.273
Mom, suddenly
I really want to go home.

19:35.275 --> 19:37.275
Oh. Mm.

19:37.277 --> 19:40.778
If you go, let me give you
one    <i>hu</i>piece of advice:

19:40.780 --> 19:42.446
take the Eighth Avenue side,

19:42.448 --> 19:44.448
then catch a cab
and circle back.

19:44.450 --> 19:46.450
And away... I... go!

19:46.452 --> 19:49.287
(scatting)
Pow!

19:49.289 --> 19:53.624
Well, Laney, youse, uh...
you still got me.

19:53.626 --> 19:55.693
♪

20:15.981 --> 20:18.149
♪

20:18.151 --> 20:20.151
See how gaudy his house is?

20:20.153 --> 20:21.819
A brass doorknocker?

20:21.821 --> 20:23.821
Who lives here, Caligula?

20:23.823 --> 20:25.323
'Tis troubling.

20:25.325 --> 20:28.326
Cousin Jacob! All the way
from Pennsyl-diddly-vania!

20:28.328 --> 20:31.329
I see thou art still using
the Devil's "diddly."

20:31.331 --> 20:33.998
Well, I must confess,
I-I do over-diddly.

20:34.000 --> 20:37.335
And I see your house is lit
by Edison's witch lights.

20:37.337 --> 20:40.838
(chuckles)
Who's holier than thou now, Ned?

20:40.840 --> 20:43.841
Homer, you've shown me that
I'm guilty of the sin of pride,

20:43.843 --> 20:46.844
and that just makes me
love you more.

20:46.846 --> 20:49.680
Oh, God,
I'm stuck in a Flandwich.

20:49.682 --> 20:51.849
With side orders
of love and forgiveness!

20:51.851 --> 20:52.917
D'oh!

21:33.058 --> 21:35.126
Shh!

21:37.562 --> 21:39.964
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH

21:42.901 --> 21:44.769
You've just watched
The Simpsons.

21:44.771 --> 21:47.171
Now here are a few more shows
to check out from Fox.

21:48.740 --> 21:51.842
(crowd cheering)

21:52.744 --> 21:54.912
MAN:
This is American Idol!

21:54.914 --> 21:57.848
(cheering continues)

21:59.785 --> 22:01.352
Absolutely fantastic.

22:05.590 --> 22:07.992
It's really about
dreams coming true.

22:07.994 --> 22:10.394
-(screaming)
-♪ I'm going to
Hollywood ♪

22:11.363 --> 22:13.964
MAN: Discover an idol
one last time.

22:13.966 --> 22:17.435
♪ (chorus vocalizing)
